events.name: Los Angeles Lakers at Orlando Magic

headlines.description: — LeBron James scored 28 points, Russell Westbrook had a triple-double and the Los Angeles Lakers stopped a four-game slide, beating the Orlando Magic 129-110 on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: James helps Lakers stop 4-game slide with win over Magic

headlines.description: — The Washington Wizards dug themselves quite a hole this month.
headlines.shortLinkText: Wizards prevail 116-111 to snap 76ers' 8-game winning streak

headlines.description: — Acting interim Boston Celtics coach Damon Stoudamire had the perfect plan for his debut in the top job.
headlines.shortLinkText: Brown (39 pts), Tatum (38) lead Celtics past Rockets 126-102

headlines.description: — Buddy Hield made six 3-pointers on his way to 28 points, and the Indiana Pacers beat the Atlanta Hawks 129-114 on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Hield makes 6 3-pointers as Pacers beat Hawks 129-114

headlines.description: — Paul George scored 23 points, Ivica Zubac had 23 points and 16 rebounds, and the Los Angeles Clippers won for the seventh time in nine games by beating the Toronto Raptors 124-113 on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: George scores 23, Clippers beat Raptors for 7th win in 9

headlines.description: — Duane Washington Jr. scored a career-high 26 points, and the Phoenix Suns beat the Memphis Grizzlies 125-108 on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Washington scores 26 as banged-up Suns beat Grizzlies

events.name: San Antonio Spurs at Oklahoma City Thunder

headlines.description: — Shai Gilgeous-Alexander had 28 points, eight assists, six rebounds and four blocked shots, and the Oklahoma City Thunder closed a season-high, seven-game homestand by beating the San Antonio Spurs 130-114 on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Thunder beat Spurs 130-114 to wrap up seven-game homestand

events.name: New York Knicks at Dallas Mavericks

headlines.description: — Luka Doncic thought his improbable tying basket in the final second of regulation actually won the game.
headlines.shortLinkText: Doncic has 60-21-10, rallies Mavs to wild OT win over Knicks

events.name: Charlotte Hornets at Golden State Warriors

headlines.description: — Jonathan Kuminga is earning more minutes for his defense, and he showed everybody the big strides he has made as a stopper with veteran Andre Iguodala as his guide and mentor.
headlines.shortLinkText: Klay Thompson scores 29, leads Warriors past Hornets 110-105

headlines.description: — Michael Porter Jr. scored 30 points, Jamal Murray added 25 and the Denver Nuggets rallied from a 20-point deficit to beat the Sacramento Kings 113-106 on Tuesday night for their fifth straight win.
headlines.shortLinkText: Nuggets rally to beat Kings 113-106 for 5th straight win
